name: Trunk Circuit Identification Code
title: TCIC
definition: Identifies a specific trunk for which CCS is being performed as assigned by the customer.
usageNotes: Required when the RT field is “F” and the TCIC field on the Trunking and/or ACI Form is populated, otherwise prohibited.
fieldNotes: This entry must be identical to the TCIC entry on the Trunking and/or ACI Form.
